title: Interest rates , Voice to parliament , NSW election : AFR 20 predictions for 2023
body_text:
It has been an astonishing few years.
Who would have predicted the world would fall back in love with nuclear power, that China would go full Maoist and then pivot, that we would be in and out of COVID-19 lockdowns for two years straight (and then resume life as normal), and that inflation would come back to haunt us all, driving up interest rates and in turn triggering the deepest property downturn on record.
